    <deploymentStatus>Deployed</deploymentStatus>
    <description>Some partners (Marketplace) from Atlassian provides us rebates and promo codes when we are quoting so we can get better margins by using those codes available.

Those codes are provided/share by the vendor mostly when we ask them if there is a code we can use, sometimes those codes are available for a certain amount of time and can be used by anyone in Eficode to apply them when creating the quote in Atlassian. after that the quote will update our costs giving us better margins.

The problem with you to solve is that by using the connection we have in place, to identify which promo codes are available and display a message to users if there is a hit when they are importing quotes so they can apply the valid code.

I was thinking about a table where we can list the partner (string) to compare with the quote import and if the expiration date in that table is still valid, then we display the message.</description>
